-- Italy Estimates EU60 Billion in Tax Evaded Last Year, Sole Says
-- B y   A r m o r e l   K e n n a
-- 2012-01-22T13:17:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-22/italy-estimates-eu60-billion-in-tax-evaded-last-year-sole-says.html
Italian finance police estimate
about 60 billion euros ($78 billion) in taxes were evaded last
year in the country, daily  Il Sole 24 Ore  reported, citing an
interview with head of the Guardia di Finanza, Nino Di Paolo.
Measures put in place by the government will help better fight
 tax evasion  in the future, the Italian newspaper cited Di Paolo
as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
